# Tool listing tiles (permanent)

All **calculation tool** listings must use compact Omni Calculator–style tiles, not large cards.

## Required components

- **`ToolTile`** (`src/components/cards/ToolTile.tsx`) — single small clickable box per tool
- **`ToolsTileGrid`** (`src/components/tools/ToolsTileGrid.tsx`) — dense responsive grid wrapper

## Rules

- Never use `ToolCard` or custom large card layouts for tool catalogs.
- Never use ad-hoc `Link` + `rounded-xl p-5` patterns for tool lists; use `ToolsTileGrid`.
- `RelatedTools`, industry hubs, pricing, free-tools, consultant pages, and search results must all use `ToolsTileGrid`.
- Industry **sector packs** (`IndustryCard`) use a compact header plus `ToolsTileGrid` for that sector’s tools.

## Grid density

Prefer `gap-2` and 2–7 columns (`grid-cols-2` → `2xl:grid-cols-7`) so tiles stay small on every breakpoint.
